content:
Bug: Router returned truncated results (47-85 chars instead of 4-6KB) for complex tasks with 7+ tools or multiple tool runs.

Root cause: createGatewayExecutor() in src/router/gateway-integration.ts line 115 used payloads[0].text, which captures the first assistant text output before any tool calls. For multi-tool runs, the payloads array contains all intermediate assistant texts, with the final answer in the last payload.

Evidence: Deleted executor session 31db245c contained full 2244-token final answer with stopReason "stop", but Router queue stored only 56 chars (first intermediate text).

Fix implemented: Changed code to iterate payloads array backwards, returning the first non-null text from the end:
for (let i = payloads.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
  if (payloads[i]?.text) return payloads[i].text;
}

Status as of 2026-03-04: Code changed but not built or pushed. 11 of 13 router tests pass; 2 failures are pre-existing Ollama timeout issues unrelated to this change. Awaiting Serj's approval to build and restart.
